uation magnitudes and mean\ngeometric parameters for the plectoneme. We see a slight asymmetry, where\ninterestingly enough left handed supercoils have looser structure than right\nhanded ones, although a lower free energy, unlike what previous ground state\ncalculations would suggest.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Sep 2016 13:35:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Oct 2016 15:08:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 13 Jan 2017 16:39:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-16"}
{"id":"1609.02422","submitter":"David Ellerman","authors":"David Ellerman","title":"What can (partition) logic contribute to information theory?","comments":"arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1301.5607","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Logical probability theory was developed as a quantitative measure based on\nBoole's logic of subsets. But information theory was developed into a mature\ntheory by Claude Shannon with no such connection to logic. A recent development\nin logic changes this situation. In category theory, the notion of a subset is\ndual to the notion of a quotient set or partition, and recently the logic of\npartitions has been developed in a parallel relationship to the Boolean logic\nof subsets (subset logic is usually mis-specified as the special case of\npropositional logic). What then is the quantitative measure based on partition\nlogic in the same sense that logical probability theory is based on subset\nlogic? It is a measure of information that is named \"logical entropy\" in view\nof that logical basis. This paper develops the notion of logical entropy and\nthe basic notions of the resulting logical information theory. Then an\nextensive comparison is made with the corresponding notions based on Shannon\nentropy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Sep 2016 13:36:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 25 Mar 2017 04:35:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-28"}
